Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is a formula then v0 is an object)

Signature:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a formula and v1 is a formula then for all v2, (if v2 is equal to v0 \imp v1 then v2 is a formula)))

Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is a formula then (if \deducible v0 then truth holds))

Axiom (detachment):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a formula and v1 is a formula then (if \deducible v0 and \deducible v0 \imp v1 then \deducible v1)))

Axiom (implosion):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a formula and v1 is a formula then \deducible v0 \imp v1 \imp v0))

Axiom (chain):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (if v0 is a formula and v1 is a formula and v2 is a formula then \deducible v0 \imp v1 \imp v2 \imp v0 \imp v1 \imp v0 \imp v2)))

Theorem (weakening):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a formula then (if \deducible v0 then for all v1, (if v1 is a formula then \deducible v1 \imp v0)))
Proof:
  \deducible Q \imp P \imp Q
  \deducible P \imp Q
Qed.

Theorem (weakeningofimplication):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a formula and v1 is a formula then (if \deducible v0 \imp v1 then for all v2, (if v2 is a formula then \deducible v2 \imp v0 \imp v2 \imp v1))))
Proof:
  \deducible P \imp Q \imp R
  \deducible P \imp Q \imp R \imp P \imp Q \imp P \imp R
  \deducible P \imp Q \imp P \imp R
Qed.

Theorem (transitivity):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (if v0 is a formula and v1 is a formula and v2 is a formula then (if \deducible v0 \imp v1 and \deducible v1 \imp v2 then \deducible v0 \imp v2))))
Proof:
  \deducible P \imp Q \imp P \imp R
  \deducible P \imp R
Qed.

Theorem (identity):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a formula then \deducible v0 \imp v0)
Proof:
  \deducible P \imp P \imp P \imp P \imp P \imp P \imp P \imp P \imp P
  \deducible P \imp P \imp P \imp P
  \deducible P \imp P \imp P \imp P \imp P
  \deducible P \imp P \imp P
  \deducible P \imp P
Qed.

Theorem:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a formula and v1 is a formula then (if \deducible v0 \imp v0 \imp v1 then \deducible v0 \imp v1)))
Proof:
  \deducible P \imp P \imp Q \imp P \imp P \imp P \imp Q
  \deducible P \imp P \imp P \imp Q
  \deducible P \imp P
  \deducible P \imp Q
Qed.

Signature (falsum):
  for all v0, (if v0 is equal to \falsum then v0 is a formula)

Axiom (doublenegation):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a formula then \deducible v0 \imp \falsum \imp \falsum \imp v0)

Theorem (explosion):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a formula then \deducible \falsum \imp v0)
Proof:
Qed.

